The paper proposes a deep convolutional neural network approach for predicting tumor growth, which involves learning cell invasion and mass-effect. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), as well as machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also involves the fusion of two subnetworks, which can be considered as a form of information integration (cs.SI).
